    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Sound of Gunfire in America</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Peggy Polenberg letter points out that liability insurance is required on cars, and should be on guns as well (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Scourge of Guns'' (editorial, Sept. 5):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''The Scourge of Guns'' (editorial, Sept. 5):</p>
        <p>Everyone in the United States who owns a vehicle is required by law to carry liability insurance. This is for the protection of the driver, passengers and the other people on the road. A car is a lethal weapon. Why doesn't Congress require liability insurance for the 190 million guns in America? If gun owners had to be personally responsible for the liability of each of their weapons, maybe they would support the laws that protect all of us and our children from accidental deaths.</p>
        <p>PEGGY POLENBERG  New York, Sept. 5, 2000</p>
      </block>
